OL,4,CSelf-driving cars to be allowed on UK
OL,5,Croads this year
OL,6, Self-driving vehicles could be allowed
OL,7, on UK roads by the end of this year,
OL,8, the government has said.
OL,10,FThe Department for Transport said
OL,11,Fautomated lane-keeping systems (ALKS)
OL,12,Fwill be the first type of hands-free
OL,13,Fdriving legalised.
OL,15,FThe technology controls the position
OL,16,Fand speed of a car in a single lane but
OL,17,Fonly up to speeds of 37mph (60km/h)
OL,19,FBut insurers have warned government's
OL,20,Fdefinition of ALKS as 'self-driving' is
OL,21,Fmisleading.
